<br>
I am partnered with a chanter, and let her know &quot;if we get an add, I will pet mez it. That should give us a bit to escape.&quot;<br>
<br>
the /tell I got back was not only sad, but so so true. &quot;Hun, my pets make yours look like a moss snake&quot;..<br>
<br>
I laugh it off, we pull..sure enough we get an add..Her pet (charmed Crystalline Golem) took on a golem and a spider, with my pet hitting too. Her pet kills one before dying, the spider is at 2% health when her charmed pet dies. a 2% health spider destroyed my full health pet. Then came and killed me and chanter. Am I *THAT* useless as a 61 mage with epic?<br>
<br>
PoP made epic mages a joke? Verant, I think it is time you looked into some SERIOUS improvements on us epic mages who have completed possibly the hardest quest in the game to receive something that is now regarded as a joke. I know 5 mages on my server who have QUIT their epic quest now, because of the lack of productivity an epic pet produces in the Planes.<br>
<br>
My suggestions fall along these lines:<br>
<br>
a. SERIOUS upgrade to current epics. Allow for enrage with them. Allow a short duration spell that enrages them, and GIVE THIS TO US..don't make us quest or exp for it as AA.<br>
b. Supply us with Epic v.2. Small quest. Or just turn in an orb to someone for a new scroll for something like &quot;Furious Orb of Mastery&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
I see Shaman's, Wizards, Enchanters and Necro's soloing in the NE corner often. Mages are a solo class too. How fair is it to us that we can solo just fine in all old world areas, but PoP, we get mocked and cannot even TRY to solo? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wezloc>Wezloc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 85<br> <font color=#333333>(2/13/03 6:33:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=471.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Verant - Epics useless in PoP</span><hr size=1> Epic pet is a joke now. I mean the longer PoP moves forward, and the more I use the new pets to more Epic becomes worthless. I have a better primary item now so I no longer wield epic, and go for days without casting it.  Epic pet had a very long run as king of the hill, but his time has come, and he just didn't hold a candle to these high level mobs. The sad thing is neither do the new pets. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The new pets just don't have the hit points. Having hit BoT now I realize how much of a joke our current pets are. They need serious damage/hp upgrades. I doubt we will ever be able to solo again. Oh expect to get hella flamed by the uber snob mages that want to make sure you never get a epic upgrade because some how that hurts them............<br>
<br>
Wezloc <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maigedenugget>Maige Denugget</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 167<br> <font color=#333333>(2/13/03 6:34:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=471.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Verant - Epics useless in PoP</span><hr size=1> They did upgrade epic pets, a lot.  They still have the highest hp of any other non-focused pet, unbuffed.  They still have one of the highest dps of any summoned pet.<br>
<br>
That being said, no pet will EVER hit as hard as the mobs VI puts out there, especially the 55+ PoP mobs which can be charmed.<br>
<br>
There is no reason for an epic upgrade, just because a chanter's charmed mob can out-damage yours.  Yes, I agree it sucks that a mob at 2% can still lay waste to your epic pet.  That's just part of the game tho.  Try slowing the mobs, and that won't happen.<br>
<br>
I've done the same thing, had epic pet up, while a druid friend charmed frogs in PoV, and we'd kill other frogs or golems.  If charm breaks, epic pet gives just enough time for us to gate out, then zone back in to try again.<br>
<br>
